cluster_relations.rel_desc: The butterfly in the egg stage develops into a caterpillar (larval stage) when the egg hatches.

qualifiers.TemporalQualifier: after a few days or weeks
qualifiers.OtherQualifier: StageOrder: egg stage precedes larval (caterpillar) stage

cluster_relations.rel_desc: The egg stage is followed by and develops into the larval (caterpillar) stage.
The larval (caterpillar) stage precedes and transforms into the pupa stage.
The pupa stage transitions into the adult butterfly life stage.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that an earlier biological life stage or form naturally develops or transitions into a subsequent life stage of the same organism.
args.justification: All four relations describe successive biological life stages of a butterfly where one stage changes into the next (egg to larva, larva to pupa, pupa to adult). They share the same directed developmental-transition semantics, so a single canonical predicate 'develops_into' is appropriate.

Each relation connects two consecutive life stages within the same organism's life cycle (egg→larva, larva→pupa, pupa→adult). This is a specific family of relations about transitions between ordered life-cycle stages, so a dedicated class 'life_cycle_stage_transition_relation' is suitable.

The core semantics are about ordered progression over time in a life cycle (one stage precedes and then becomes the next). This is primarily temporal sequencing of states of the same entity, so the broad group 'TEMPORALITY' best fits.
